PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Minimal Response of Multiple Myeloma or Plasma Cell Leukemia

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Minimal Response of Multiple Myeloma or Plasma Cell Leukemia
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Patients in whom some, but not all, the criteria for partial response are fulfilled are classified as minimal response (MR), provided the remaining criteria satisfy the requirements for minimal response.  MR requires all of the following: 1. 25-49% reduction in the level of the serum monoclonal paraprotein maintained for a minimum of 6 weeks; 2. 50-89% reduction in 24 h urinary light chain excretion, which still exceeds 200 mg/24 h, maintained for a minimum of 6 weeks; 3. for patients with non-secretory myeloma only, 25-49% reduction in plasma cells in a bone marrow aspirate and on trephine biopsy, if biopsy is performed, maintained for a minimum of 6 weeks; 4. 25-49% reduction in the size of soft tissue plasmacytomas (by radiography or clinical examination); 5. no increase in size or number of lytic bone lesions (development of a compression fracture does not exclude response) (adapted from National Comprehensive Cancer Network).

Concepts.definition: Patients in whom some, but not all, the criteria for partial response are fulfilled are classified as minimal response (MR), provided the remaining criteria satisfy the requirements for minimal response.  MR requires all of the following: 1. 25-49% reduction in the level of the serum monoclonal paraprotein maintained for a minimum of 6 weeks; 2. 50-89% reduction in 24 h urinary light chain excretion, which still exceeds 200 mg/24 h, maintained for a minimum of 6 weeks; 3. for patients with non-secretory myeloma only, 25-49% reduction in plasma cells in a bone marrow aspirate and on trephine biopsy, if biopsy is performed, maintained for a minimum of 6 weeks; 4. 25-49% reduction in the size of soft tissue plasmacytomas (by radiography or clinical examination); 5. no increase in size or number of lytic bone lesions (development of a compression fracture does not exclude response) (adapted from National Comprehensive Cancer Network).

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: No new lesions; less than 50% reduction but less than 25% increase in any existing lesion (exclude bone marrow evaluation).

Concepts.definition: No new lesions; less than 50% reduction but less than 25% increase in any existing lesion (exclude bone marrow evaluation).

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: No evidence of primary tumor, no evidence of metastases (chest, abdomen, liver, bone, bone marrow, nodes, etc.), and HVA/VMA normal.

Concepts.definition: No evidence of primary tumor, no evidence of metastases (chest, abdomen, liver, bone, bone marrow, nodes, etc.), and HVA/VMA normal.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Fifty to 90% reduction of primary tumor; 50% or greater reduction in measurable sites of metastases; 0-1 bone marrow samples with tumor; number of positive bone sites decreased by greater than 50%.

Concepts.definition: Fifty to 90% reduction of primary tumor; 50% or greater reduction in measurable sites of metastases; 0-1 bone marrow samples with tumor; number of positive bone sites decreased by greater than 50%.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Very Good Partial Response in Neuroblastoma

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Very Good Partial Response in Neuroblastoma
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Greater than 90% reduction of primary tumor; no metastatic tumor (as above except bone); no new bone lesions, all pre-existing lesions improved on bone scan; HVA/VMA normal.

Concepts.longName: Very Good Partial Response in Neuroblastoma
Concepts.definition: Greater than 90% reduction of primary tumor; no metastatic tumor (as above except bone); no new bone lesions, all pre-existing lesions improved on bone scan; HVA/VMA normal.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Any component (i.e., soft tissue, bone, and bone marrow disease) with progressive disease.

Concepts.definition: Any component (i.e., soft tissue, bone, and bone marrow disease) with progressive disease. (J Clin Oncol 35: 2580-2587, 2017)
